      • blame

        protected abstract Map<String,BlameRequest> blame(Map<String,BlameRequest> linesOfConflictingFiles)
                                           throws InterruptedException,
                                                  IOException
        Computes for each conflicting file a BlameRequest. Note that this call is executed on a build agent. I.e., the blamer instance and all transfer objects need to be serializable.
        Parameters:
        linesOfConflictingFiles - a mapping of file names to blame request. Each blame request defines the lines that need to be mapped to an author.
        Returns:
        the same mapping, now filled with blame information
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if this operation has been canceled
        IOException - in case of an error

      • extractConflictingFiles

        protected Map<String,BlameRequest> extractConflictingFiles(Set<FileAnnotation> annotations)
        Extracts the relative file names of the files that contain annotations to make sure every file is blamed only once.
        Parameters:
        annotations - the annotations to extract the file names from
        Returns:
        a mapping of absolute to relative file names of the conflicting files
